I have been patronizing this establishment for 3 almost 4 years.  Today, I had an experience that will keep me from ever returning.  My co-worker and I ordered nachos to share and added additional toppings to our order.  When we returned to the office, we realized the extra veggies and black beans that we were charged extra for were left out of the bag.  When my co-worker returned to store to get what we had paid for, the guy at the counter stopped helping customers and proceed to tell her that they gave us the items. She again told him that the items were not in the bag.  I can personally vouch that we never received the items.  The guy then proceeded to say that he would not do this again because he knows they gave us the items.  As faithful customers, we have no reason to lie and are well able to pay for anything that we want or order.  I am extremely disappointed in this experience because up until today, we always received great customer service.  Arguing with a customer and accusing them of lying is not a good move, especially when they are right and telling the truth!

I still need to go over other items in the menu but so far everything has been really good. Flavor water is my way to go but I also enjoy Jarritos or a mundet. There are two reasons I give 4  stars: a) sometimes the chicken gets overcooked and is dry, but still full of flavor and chicken milanesa still my favorite taco b) they use too much of the single-use plastic like water cups, plastic ware, straws and plates, and I'd like to not feel guilty for going to a place like that. The rest of my party had their chicken quesadilla and a beef burrito and they both enjoyed theirs just as much. I don't think anyone left a bite on their plate, and we all commented later on in the day that it was perfectly portioned. We never felt too full or sluggish afterwards, but left very satisfied.
